  <title>Hydraulics</title>

  <para>The ship's hydraulic system is powered by a permanently engaged pump
  connected to the gearbox power take-off port.</para>

  <para>Pressurised oil is pumped to an adjacent storage and distribution
  unit. The unit includes an 'orbitrol' system for assisted steering and two
  electrically operated distribution valves: a low pressure valve feeds the
  anchor windlass motor and mast hydraulic cylinder and a high-pressure system
  feeds the bow-thruster motor. </para>
</section>
